Network Rail to Pass Power to Regional Heads, Sunday Times Says

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-02-20T08:15:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-20/network-rail-to-pass-power-to-regional-heads-sunday-times-says.html
Network Rail Ltd., the U.K. owner of
train tracks and stations, will transfer authority to nine
regional managing directors, the  Sunday Times  reported, without
saying where it got the information.  Each regional manager will have a budget of 800 million
pounds ($1.3 billion) and responsibility for about 3,000 staff,
according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Kay in London at 
 ckay5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  